;The small molecule is progesterone.

;Summary:
'''Progesterone''' is a steroid hormone<ref name="wiki">Progesterone. (n.d.). In ''Wikipedia''. Retrieved December 2, 2019, from https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Progesterone</ref>. It functions by affecting cellular signal transduction.

Progesterone binds to the protein progesterone receptor. This results in a cascade of downstream effects, leading to changes in the expression of various genes<ref name="pubchem">PubChem Identifier: CID 5994. Retrieved December 2, 2019, from https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/compound/5994</ref>.

Progesterone inhibits estrogen by decreasing the expression of estrogen receptors as well as increasing the metabolism of estrogens<ref name="pubchem" />.

Progesterone is often known to be involved in female reproductive physiology (i.e. the menstrual cycle)<ref name="wiki" /><ref name="pubchem" />.

